  "text": "Two major but different mechanisms are known [CITATION_1] ): Both mechanisms lead to a reduction of the radicals but differ in kinetics and propensity for side reactions [CITATION_2] ). For hydrogen atom transfer, the antioxidants quench the free radicals by donating a hydrogen whereas for single electron transfer the antioxidants transfer one electron to the radical.",
